            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here's the latest information on London Underground service updates for December 2025:\n\n1. **General Service Information**:\n   - Most London Underground services are running as usual. However, planned closures and service changes are expected around Christmas and the New Year period [TfL Service Status](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/planned-track-closures).\n\n2. **Specific Line Closures**:\n   - The Northern Line will have part closures during certain times. No service between Golders Green and Edgware on December 13-14, with replacement bus services available [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/).\n   - Piccadilly Line will be closed between Rayners Lane and Uxbridge from December 24 to January 4 [TimeOut](https://www.timeout.com/london/things-to-do/transport-in-london-over-christmas-and-new-years-eve).\n\n3. **Holiday Service Changes**:\n   - Services will end early on Christmas Eve, with no TfL services running on Christmas Day except Santander Cycles and some taxi services [TfL Christmas Travel](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/major-works-and-events/christmas-and-new-year-travel).\n\n4. **New Year’s Eve**:\n   - Overnight services will operate on New Year's Eve to accommodate festive activities. Some buses and services may be diverted due to road closures [London World](https://www.londonworld.com/news/tfl-christmas-travel-schedule-2025-5427070).\n\nAlways check for live updates before you travel, via the official TfL website or apps to ensure you have the latest information.",
